Instructions
Complete the exercise below in a group of 2-3.

Submit a link to a public Git repo that contains your scripts and a README.md that includes links to the specific documenation you used for each script.

Git repo name: "lab-week3-aws-cli"

Create your scripts using AWS CLI Command Reference documentation: 

https://awscli.amazonaws.com/v2/documentation/api/latest/index.html

Example format for documentation

script 1:
- link-to-relevant-documenation-section

Starter files: https://gitlab.com/cit_4640/4640-w3-lab-start-w25

Script 1.

Write a script that will "import" the public key from a locally created key pair into your AWS account. 

Name your key "bcitkey". You need this for script 3.

Script 2.

Complete the create-bucket script included in the starter files

Notes: 
pay attention to the documentation on --create-bucket-configuration LocationConstraint

Remember that bucket names must be unique.

You can delete your bucket with the command

aws s3api delete-bucket --bucket <your-bucket-name> --region us-west-2

Script 3 and 4

copy the create-vpc and create-ec2 scripts from the starter files

Complete the create-vpc and create-ec2 scripts, see comments in scripts

- use the AMI provided by the "debian_ami" variable
- use the security group provided by the "security_group_id" variable.
- use the key pair you imported above in part 1.
- write the public IP address of your EC2 instance to a new "instance_data" file.

After you have provisioned your infrastructure with these scripts test that you can connect to your EC2 instance via ssh using the key you created in part 2.

Include a note on D2L with your group members names.
